<TITLE> SC lawyers discuss legal aid to Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 22 (bdnews24.com)  A section of Supreme Court lawyers held a meeting Sunday to discuss ways of giving legal assistance for detained Awami League chief Sheikh Hasina, a lawyer said. After the meeting, the lawyers said they discussed if they would file a petition to quash the extortion case against Hasina, who was arrested on July 26. The meeting was held in the Supreme Court Bar Association office, attended by former SCBA chief Mahbubey Alam, former law minister Abdul Matin Khasru, Enayetur Rahim, Bangladesh Bar Council executive committee chairman Yusuf Hossain Humayun, Shamsul Huda Manik, Mamatazuddin Ahmed, senior advocate Ali Haider Khan, Rahmat Ali, Sajwar Hossain, Aminuddin and advocate Nurul Islam Sujan. They also prayed for Hasina after the meeting. Earlier, 515 lawyers from Chittagong Lawyers Association and 81 from Jhalkathi demanded release of the former prime minister. They expressed deep concern over the arrest of Hasina. In a statement, Jhalkathi lawyers described the arrest as a shameful act Chittagong lawyers said the arrest of Hasina raised questions about the transparency of the anticorruption drive and commitment of holding fair polls by the government. They termed the case against Hasina false and said it was part of the government's conspiracy to implement the so-called 'minus-2 formula'. bdnews24.co
